description:
In what is likely to be the hardest cycle of the entire journey, we begin by making our way over the first of two mountain ranges by heading west from Echizen via route 19. We then head south on route 206 for the last part of the climb, before rolling down the other side of the mountain - emerging on the east coast and the Sea of Japan. With amazing views of the ocean to our right, we follow the coast south before reaching the port town of Tsuruga for lunch.

We then begin the real challenge; a 1000 metre climb over the mountains separating the Fukui and Shiga prefectures. After what I imagine will be a lot of breaks and a lot of pushing, we then roll down the other side via a long winding gravel road before reaching Lake Biwa and the small town of Makino.
